## âš™ï¸ 2ï¸âƒ£ PCB Layout Design

### ğŸ§­ Open PCB Editor
- Open the **PCB Editor (Pcbnew)**  
- Click **Update PCB from Schematic** to import all footprints and nets  

### ğŸ§© Arrange Components
- Move and rotate components for compact and logical placement  
- Keep related connectors close and oriented properly  

### ğŸ“ Define Board Outline
- Use **Edge.Cuts layer** â†’ draw rectangular board boundary  
- Example: `100mm Ã— 30mm`  

### âš™ï¸ Place Mounting Holes (Optional)
- Add **3.2mm holes** at board corners  
*(e.g., MountingHole_3.2mm_M3)*  

### ğŸ”€ Route Traces
- Choose **Route â†’ Interactive Router (X)**  
- Use:
- **Top Layer (F.Cu)** for signal traces *(red)*  
- **Bottom Layer (B.Cu)** for ground/return paths *(blue)*  
- Adjust track width:
- Power lines â†’ `1mm` or more  
- Signals â†’ `0.25â€“0.4mm`  

### ğŸ§² Add Copper Fill
- Add a **Ground Plane (GND)**  
- Use **Add Filled Zone â†’ Select GND net â†’ Apply to both layers**  
- Press `B` to refill zones  

### ğŸ” Design Rule Check (DRC)
- Run **Inspect â†’ Design Rules Checker**  
- Fix any clearance, unconnected, or short errors  

### âœï¸ Add Silkscreen
- Add **text labels**, **component names**, and **project title**  
- Keep text inside board boundaries  

